      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a vital constitutional tool that protects fundamental liberties against government overreach, ensuring that the government cannot infringe upon core rights even if it follows proper legal procedures. It has been instrumental in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that infringe upon personal autonomy, such as those concerning privacy and bodily integrity. This doctrine affirms that certain rights are so fundamental they are inherent to liberty and cannot be taken away by legislative action.",
