      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The landmark case *Griswold v. Connecticut* is a perfect example, establishing a constitutional right to marital privacy that the government could not violate. Furthermore, *Roe v. Wade* used substantive due process to protect a woman's right to choose, fundamentally reshaping reproductive freedom in America. These decisions demonstrate the judiciary's power to recognize and enforce deeply held personal liberties against legislative intrusion.",
      "source": "target",
